For this, we will use the concept of present value annuity which is the present value of future payments based on the rate and time given. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\dfrac{\text{Future value}}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}
\end{aligned}$$

Now, we can solve for the present value of the annual savings using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\text{Cashflow} \times \dfrac{1-\left(\frac{1+\text{growth rate}}{1+\text{return rate}}\right)^\text{time}}{\text{return rate}-\text{growth rate}}
\end{aligned}$$
